s from 200\nto 3000 AU and eccentricities smaller than 0.8, approximately. The oscillation\nperiods for these orbits range from 10^5 to 2 x 10^6 years, approximately.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Dec 2010 17:09:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Jun 2011 16:39:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2011 18:35:12 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 1 Sep 2011 12:42:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-01"}
